The paper deals with the problem of cooperative path finding (CPF) which involves multiple agents moving in an undirected graph. This problem is commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI), multi-agent systems (MA), robotics (RO), and logic (LG). The paper also discusses the use of propositional satisfiability (SAT) for solving CPF, which is a common technique in the field of programming languages and compilers (PL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.LG, and cs.PL.
